**SYSTEM INFO**
uname -a 
free -h
duf #(table formatted disk usage)
ncdu <directory name> (directories in decreasing disk usage)
nc (netcat, investigate sockets)
du -h --max-depth=1 <filename>
glances (cpu, mem, disk io, other)
lshw (list of hardware)
dstats
systemd-analyze blame (how long an initial process takes to load)
env (list of environment variables, might be listenv instead of env)
nmon (menu for CPU, memory, disk, utilization and others)
  --other--
cowsay message 
sl (running train, ls mispelled)
asciiquarium (aquarium in terminal)
espeak hello (make computer say hello)
fortune (random fortune message
figlet word (display large banner with text/word)
cmatrix (like the movie)
hollywood (multiple screens with random output)

